y we compute the\ncorrections to the Coulomb's law for a more general case, on a thick brane\nscenario, for which we can do estimates consistent with brane phenomenology,\ni.e. we found that the predicted corrections to the Coulomb law in our model,\nwhich are well bounded by the observed experimental photon mass, is far beyond\nits upper bound, positively testing the viability of our tachyonic braneworld.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Dec 2014 17:59:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-25"}
