}$) below $T_{\\rm N}$, and the exponent\n($\\alpha$) decreases from 3 in the parent compound to 1 in the 25\\% doped\nsample.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Dec 2014 09:46:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 Jul 2015 04:58:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-08"}
