1422\\,\\mathrm{MeV}/c^2$ and\n$\\Gamma = 130-150\\,\\mathrm{MeV}/c^2$. In the same analysis, a signal in a wave\nwith $J^{PC}=1^{-+}$ is observed. A resonant origin of this signal would not be\nexplicable within the CQM. In addition to this possibility of an exotic state,\na possible non resonant origin of this signal is discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Dec 2014 13:24:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-07"}
